Project Overview
The To-Do List Application allows users to manage tasks efficiently, supporting functionalities such as adding, editing, deleting, and categorizing tasks into "To Do," "Doing," and "Done" lists.

Documentation to Run the Project:-

-> Build Steps
Although there are no complex build steps required for this project, here are some suggested enhancements you might consider in the future:

Transpilation :
Use tools like Babel to transpile ES6+ code to ensure compatibility with older browsers.
Command: npx babel src --out-dir dist

Bundling :
Consider using Webpack to bundle JavaScript files, optimizing loading times.
Command: npx webpack --config webpack.config.js

Linting:
Use ESLint to maintain code quality and consistency.
Command: npx eslint .


-> How to Run the Project
Clone the Repository:
Use the following command to clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/todo-list-app.git

Navigate to Project Directory:
cd todo-list-app

Open the Application:
Open index.html in your preferred web browser.

Demo Link
You can view the live demo of the To-Do List Application at the following link:
https://to-do-application-adityarathore.netlify.app/

